at|mitche:  Play:  How should N/S defend?
North was correct to try the @SK first and in response to South's 4, the @HA at trick 2 is also correct, 
but since South bid just 2@h, she should have only 3 of them.  
With 4 hearts, we use Bergen raises.
So North should lead a heart at trick 3. 
If West started with the @HKQx, then too bad, 5@C is always making.|
