nt||at|True, that South should play her most encouraging heart. But North should still play a heart at trick 3.
North knows that West began with 2 hearts (or should, if N/S use Bergen .. see above).
If North is worried that a heart will get ruffed, she should try to cash the @SK at trick 3.|
pg| ***** 113 ***** |


nt||at| But no matter what North does at trick 3, it should not be a diamond. 
There is no way that West can possibly get rid of a diamond loser if she has one. 
Remember that 4@d showed a big minor 2-suiter, so a @D can only help declarer.

Next point: As declarer you need to count the cards in suits you are trying to set up, and watch the high cards. |
