at|mitche: When the defense shifted to a @D at trick 3, declarer was able to discard a heart from dummy and ruff a heart.  
She also managed to establish the @d suit, so the @d10 was a winner, 
and all she needed to do was ruff a spade at trick 11 and her hand was high.
Please remember to count the cards at least in trumps and the side suit you want to set up.

I recommend an easy way to do that:|
pg| ***** 115 ***** |


nt||at|Start by counting the number of cards the defenders hold in your key (@d) suit. 
Each time the suit is played, decrease the count. 
So West can  start with - the defenders have J987xx outstanding.
Declarer played 3 rounds of the suit and on the first 2, both defenders followed, leaving 2 outstanding. 
AND the jack fell, making the 10 high. Now the third round left just 1 @D  out, and the 10 will pull it, 
establishing the 6 and 5 as winners.|
